x4freetext: Atomic beam polarized-ion source.
Beam polarization 0.84 for E<5.4 MeV, 0.333 for
E>5.4 MeV.
36Ar ions implanted onto C foil with evaporated Au
coating.
6 Hamamatsu Si PIN detectors places symetrically on
either side of beam at 6 angles.
Beam polarization measured continuously with 4He
polarimeter mounted at back of scattering chamber.
Data received by email from N. Kaloskamis, 26 Nov 1998.
Approved by Kaloskamis, March 15, 1999.
Author approval added.

reacs.QuantHlp: Differential c/s with respect to angle

x4freetext: Relative cross sections
calculated by normalizing the area of the 36Ar group
to the area of the 197Au group and assuming that
197Au scattering was purely Rutherford.
Absolute cross section normalized by fitting resonance
at 5018 keV known to have GAMMA(p) = GAMMA(total).
Statistical uncertainty
